# Multilingual Content Synchronization

## Content Update Rules

### Universal Updates
When updating content in one language, ensure corresponding files in other languages are updated to maintain consistency across:

- `index.md`
- `en/**/*`
- `ru/**/*` 
- `ua/**/*`
- `es/**/*`
- `_includes/en/**/*`
- `_includes/ru/**/*`
- `_includes/ua/**/*`
- `_includes/es/**/*`

### Navigation Updates
When adding or removing content sections or referencing articles from index pages, update navigation and references accordingly in:

- `index.md`
- `ru/index.md`
- `ua/index.md`
- `es/index.md`

## Consistency Requirements
- Maintain identical structure across all language versions
- Ensure all navigation links work in every language
- Keep article organization consistent between languages
- Update all index files when adding new content sections
